Available on our Facebook page here
Funny & informative onboard experience
Lockboxes for valuables and clothes
The #1 Jet Boat Ride on Airlie Beach
Come get WET on Wild Thing
This truly is the “Ultimate Jet Boat Experience”
Zoom past the Coral Sea Marina & Resort; Perform 360 & 180 spins, power stops, drifts and nosedives; all while taking in the magnificent views of the Whitsundays. Cruise around the stunning blue waters of Pioneer Bay. Each tour is crammed with so much action & laughter its guaranteed to be the highlight of your day and stay in Airlie Beach!
What to Expect on Your Airlie Beach Jet Boat Ride
Hold on tight as you zoom along the coast and speed out across Pioneer Bay. Listen to the onboard commentary as you pass the glitzy seafront mansions and look out over the distant Whitsundays islands. All while feeling the surges of adrenaline as your expert pilot performs daring 180/360 degree spins, drifts and power brake stops. Woo!
After an exhilarating ride, look out for wildlife such as sea turtles, dugongs, and stingrays, as you glide back to shore.
We provide everything you need for the Ultimate Airlie Beach Jet Boat Tour!
We have lock boxes/small luggage storage for your valuables
Spray glasses (yes, they’re cooler than your ray bans)
Lifejackets and Spray jackets
Funny and informative commentary
FREE GoPro photos to remember the experience! Find them
Airlie Beach Jet Boat Highlights
30 min Jetboat ride around Pioneer Bay from Airlie Beach
The ultimate mix of laughter, water & adrenaline
Experience daring stunts including 180 and 360 turns, power stops and drifts
Spot wildlife like turtles, dugongs, and stingrays around the bay
Free photos available on our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/PioneerAdventuresTours
No experience necessary: suitable for all ages (over 5) and abilities
Choice of morning or afternoon departure
We provide a small storage section for things that must stay dry
It this tour suitable for families?
What can I bring on board?
No loose items can be taken on board E.g. Cameras, hats etc. They must be left in the storage boxes provided.
What should I wear?
You are going to get wet so wear swimmers or clothing that can get wet and bring a towel to dry off.
What if I have a medical condition?
This tour is not suitable for travellers with back or neck problems, heart problems, pregnancy or other serious medical conditions.
Is this tour wheelchair accessible?
Unfortunately, this tour is not wheelchair accessible.
Do you offer a bus pick up?
What if it is raining?
Will you cancel my trip?
This experience requires a minimum number of travellers. If it’s cancelled because the minimum isn’t met, you’ll be offered a different date/experience or a full refund
Departure Point for Your Jet Boat Ride on Airlie Beach
The activity starts and begins at this departure point
Airlie Beach is a popular basecamp for visiting the Whitsundays and the Great Barrier Reef, but there are plenty of opportunities for adventure activities without leaving town. Our Airlie Beach Jet Boat Tour is the perfect choice for you if your time is limited in tropical North Queensland.
AIRLIE BEACH GLASS BOTTOM BOAT DAY TOURS
8 am - 5 pm
We acknowledge the traditional custodians, the Ngaro, Gia and Juru people of the land. We pay our respects to the Elders past and present, for they hold the memories, the traditions, the culture and hopes of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples across the nation.
