Discover local Coral Reefs & Marine Life on our Airlie Beach Glass Bottom Boat Tour in The Whitsundays
Airlie Beach Glass Bottom Boat Tour Overview
Join us on our unique Glass Bottom Boat Tour discovering Airlie Beach’s most spectacular coral reefs! This tour explores the valuable ecosystem that lives within the gateway to the Great Barrier Reef. Provides the perfect
learning experience about the diverse ecosystems that make up The Great Barrier Reef.
Get up close and personal with a colourful spectrum of vibrant hard & soft corals, fish & other marine life; all while you cruise through the idyllic islands of The Whitsundays.
Our Airlie Beach Glass Bottom Boat
allows you to immerse yourself in the spectacular underwater world, without getting wet! This tour is suited for all age groups; perfect for family, friends or solo travellers. Get up close and personal with a wide variety of marine life. Our shaded vessel ‘Bottoms Up’ is a custom made for coral reef viewing.
We are excited to announce we now feature a photo opportunity stop at Lions Lookout prior to Glass Bottom Boat Departure. Marvel at the views over the harbour and the stunning Whitsunday islands and add to your holiday photo collection!
